# 📄 Statement of Work (SOW)
Penetration Testing Engagement

---

## 📌 Overview

This Statement of Work (SOW) defines the specific scope, targets, and deliverables for the penetration testing engagement.

This document works alongside the main Penetration Testing Agreement.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

The objectives of this engagement are to:

- Identify security vulnerabilities in defined systems
- Assess real-world exploitability
- Evaluate security controls (firewalls, IDS)
- Provide actionable remediation recommendations

---

## 🧪 Scope of Testing

### In-Scope Assets

- Internal IT Department VLAN
- Operations and logistics servers
- Development environment (SQL testing only)

---

### Out-of-Scope Assets

- Production SQL databases
- Any system not explicitly listed
- Third-party systems without authorization

---

## 🧰 Testing Types

The following testing activities are authorized:

- Internal network penetration testing
- Vulnerability scanning
- Configuration review
- Limited SQL testing (development environment only)

---

### Restricted Activities

- Social engineering limited to provided email addresses only
- No testing beyond approved targets
- No destructive testing on production systems

---

## 🕒 Timeline

- Start Date: Two weeks from agreement signing
- Testing Duration: Up to 60 days
- Reporting: Final report delivered at end of engagement

---

## 📍 Location of Testing

- Primary Location: Houston Facility
- Remote/Internal Testing via VLAN access

---

## 📦 Deliverables

The following deliverables will be provided:

- Initial Findings Report
- Full Technical Report
- Executive Summary
- Vulnerability Risk Register
- Remediation Recommendations

---

## 👥 Client Responsibilities

The Client agrees to:

- Provide necessary access to systems
- Ensure systems are backed up before testing
- Provide test accounts where required
- Notify internal teams of testing activities

---

## 🔐 Confidentiality

All findings and data obtained during testing will be treated as confidential and handled according to agreed data protection standards.

---

## ⚠️ Disclaimer

This SOW is for educational purposes and does not constitute legal advice.

